article.headline: Central Arkansas 34, Georgia Southern 31, OT
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- James Paul kicked a 25-yard field goal in overtime to give Central Arkansas a 34-31 victory over Georgia Southern on Saturday. Paul had a chance to win the game in regulation, but missed a 22-yard attempt with 4:36 remaining. Georgia Southern kicker Jonathan Dudley also had an opportuntity to win the game, but he missed from 32 yards with 46 seconds left in regulation. The Eagles (3-8) got the ball first in overtime, and facing a fourth-and-three at the Central Arkansas (8-3) chose not to attempt a kick. Quarterback Travis Clark's pass fell incomplete, and the Bears then took possession at the 25. Central Arkansas, in its first year in Division I-AA, moved the ball to the 8-yard line and fourth down sent in Paul. This time he delivered to hand the Eagles their fifth straight loss. Georgia Southern, suffering its first losing season since 1996, lost six games by a total of 21 points, including two in overtime. Nathan Brown completed 18 of 31 passes for 279 yards and three touchdowns for Central Arkansas, which had only 90 yards rushing. Lamar Lewis ran for 99 yards for Georgia Southern which had 183 yards rushing. Quarterback Travis Clark completed 8 of 20 passes for 177 yards. The game got off to a rousing start when Cameron Kinard took the opening kickoff about 3 yards deep in the end zone and returned it for a touchdown. Georgia Southern countered with a 10-play 72 yard drive to tie it on a 1-yard run by Lamar Lewis. The Eagles then showed their big play ability when Jayson Foster fielded a punt on the 22-yard line and weaved his way 78 yards to give Georgia Southern a 14-7 lead. Foster made it 20-7 in the second period when he ran 39 yards for his second touchdown. Brown threw two touchdown passes in the second period, one for four yards to Preston Echols and then for 14 yards to Brent Grimes for a 21-20 lead. Following Grimes score Georgia Southern wasted no time in taking a 28-21 halftime lead as Clark caught Darius Smiley in the open and hit him on a 74-yard scoring strike. Dudley kicked a 37-yard field goal to start the second half, but Paul countered with a 21-yard field goal and Grimes caught a 27-yard scoring pass from Brown with 7:43 remaining to make it 31-31.
